1
00:00:32,241 --> 00:00:35,411
片名：爱国者游戏

2
00:02:13,009 --> 00:02:15,011
（雷恩家）

3
00:02:39,661 --> 00:02:41,329
我们现在不便接听电话
Sorry, we can't come to the phone right now.

4
00:02:41,412 --> 00:02:44,040
请留言，我们稍后将回电
If you leave a message we'll get back to you as soon as we can.

5
00:02:44,165 --> 00:02:45,291
谢谢
Thanks.

6
00:02:46,709 --> 00:02:48,211
梅米，我是杰克
Hi, Mamie. It's Jack.

7
00:02:48,336 --> 00:02:50,380
我们会按原计划离开伦敦
We're going to leave London as planned,

8
00:02:50,505 --> 00:02:52,131
我们会搭计程车回家
but we'll take a cab from the airport,

9
00:02:52,215 --> 00:02:54,384
不用麻烦别人开车来接我们了
so nobody has to bother to drive in and pick us up.

10
00:02:55,718 --> 00:02:57,095
- 我们需要买点东西…  - 八
- We need a light shop done. - Eight.

11
00:02:57,178 --> 00:02:59,180
给家里留一点东西，牛奶、鸡蛋、面包
A few things to have in the house, milk, eggs, bread.

12
00:02:59,264 --> 00:03:00,598
一、二、三、四、五、六、七…
One, two, three, four, five, six, seven...

13
00:03:00,682 --> 00:03:02,725
凯瑟琳想知道你是否能带回干洗衣物
Catherine wants to know if you can pick up the dry cleaning.

14
00:03:02,851 --> 00:03:04,811
那个已经是你的了 你什么都有了
You already own that. You own everything.

15
00:03:04,894 --> 00:03:07,355
我们之前来不及购物
We didn't get that before we left.

16
00:03:07,564 --> 00:03:10,233
我们把莎莉的金鱼忘到九霄云外了
And listen, we completely forgot about Sally's goldfish.

17
00:03:10,358 --> 00:03:12,318
假使它们还活着…
If by some miracle they're still alive,

18
00:03:12,402 --> 00:03:13,987
请你帮忙放饲料及换水
will you feed them and change the water, and...

19
00:03:14,070 --> 00:03:16,865
让妈妈替我走一步
Um, Mom will make my move, honey.

20
00:03:17,574 --> 00:03:18,867
若已经死了，看你能不能到商店
And if they're not, will you go to the store

21
00:03:18,950 --> 00:03:22,704
买到差不多的鱼？
and see if you can find a couple that are sort of the same size?

22
00:03:23,705 --> 00:03:25,582
好的，一会见
Okay, we'll see you soon. Bye.

23
00:03:26,249 --> 00:03:28,167
- 一，二，三，四…  - 怎么了？
- One, two, three, four... - What's happening?

24
00:03:28,251 --> 00:03:31,045
…五，六！真棒
...five, six! Yes!

25
00:03:31,588 --> 00:03:32,797
不
Oh, no.

26
00:03:34,424 --> 00:03:35,717
又一间饭店？
Another hotel?

27
00:03:36,467 --> 00:03:37,677
他欠你多少？
What does... What does he owe you?

28
00:03:37,760 --> 00:03:42,015
你欠我1100英镑@
You owe me 1,100.

29
00:03:42,098 --> 00:03:43,933
我没钱了，你赢了
I haven't got it. You win.

30
00:03:44,058 --> 00:03:45,476
- 我出局了  - 这小女孩真有钱
- I'm out. - This girl is rich.

31
00:03:45,560 --> 00:03:47,061
我想去睡觉了
I want to go to sleep.

32
00:03:59,282 --> 00:04:00,742
晚安，先生
Good evening, sir.

33
00:04:01,409 --> 00:04:02,410
什么事？
Yes?

34
00:04:02,493 --> 00:04:03,995
这些可以吗？
Will these do?

35
00:04:07,457 --> 00:04:09,125
好，送进来吧
Yeah. Bring them in.

36
00:04:10,919 --> 00:04:12,253
一定是我太太要的
My wife, I guess.

37
00:04:34,609 --> 00:04:36,819
蜡烛，香槟…
Candles, champagne...

38
00:04:36,945 --> 00:04:38,279
亲爱的
Oh, honey.

39
00:04:39,322 --> 00:04:41,240
抱歉我没想到这个
I'm sorry, I didn't think of this.

40
00:04:41,324 --> 00:04:42,659
没关系
That's all right.

41
00:04:42,784 --> 00:04:44,452
我们当中有一个想到就行
Only one of us had to.

42
00:04:48,039 --> 00:04:49,499
她睡了吗？
Is she asleep?

43
00:05:00,635 --> 00:05:02,387
讲稿准备好了吗？
What about your speech?

44
00:05:02,637 --> 00:05:03,972
到时再即兴发挥吧
I'll wing it.

45
00:05:04,389 --> 00:05:05,640
你确定？
You sure?

46
00:05:14,190 --> 00:05:16,609
我们都非常关注着
We have all watched, I think, with a sense of awe,

47
00:05:16,693 --> 00:05:18,319
在莫斯科和各个联邦国家
the protean events which have taken place

48
00:05:18,403 --> 00:05:20,321
所发生的一连串事件
in Moscow and the Republics

49
00:05:20,989 --> 00:05:24,409
这些事件所引发的巨大变化
and the enormous changes resulting from these events.

50
00:05:25,243 --> 00:05:26,869
在当前不稳定的政治气候下
In this volatile climate, then,

51
00:05:26,995 --> 00:05:29,372
我的结论是我们仅能限于推测
I must conclude that we can only speculate

52
00:05:29,497 --> 00:05:33,126
关于苏联舰队未来的发展与部署
on the future of Soviet fleet development and deployment.

53
00:05:33,209 --> 00:05:35,962
我想感谢皇家海军官校的理事
I would like to thank the trustees of the Royal Naval Academy

54
00:05:36,045 --> 00:05:39,674
热情地邀约今天到此与诸位共度
for their very kind invitation to be here with you today.

55
00:06:43,738 --> 00:06:46,282
他很欣赏你，莎莉，他不能表现出来
He's impressed, Sally. He just can't show it.

56
00:06:46,407 --> 00:06:47,867
他是个职业卫兵
He's a professional soldier.

57
00:06:47,950 --> 00:06:50,119
他不能被任何事干扰
It's his job not to be distracted.

58
00:06:50,828 --> 00:06:53,414
走吧，我们去接爸爸
Come on. We've got to go meet Daddy.

59
00:06:54,499 --> 00:06:56,000
你很了不起
I'm impressed.

60
00:07:04,592 --> 00:07:06,052
找到了吗？
Find it on the map there?

61
00:07:06,135 --> 00:07:07,428
- 好  - 我们在这儿
- Good. - We're right here.

62
00:07:07,512 --> 00:07:10,264
到了前面的街再向左转
And when we get to the street there, we turn left...

63
00:07:10,348 --> 00:07:11,891
不，右边，对，向右
No, right. Yeah, right.

64
00:07:11,974 --> 00:07:13,101
- 确定吗？  - 对，向右转
- You sure? - Turn right, yes.

65
00:07:13,184 --> 00:07:15,603
那就向右转，跟着你的地图走
Okay, we're going to turn right. I'm following your map.

66
00:07:15,686 --> 00:07:17,605
没问题
Okay, okay, all right.

67
00:07:30,618 --> 00:07:32,703
你要多加小心，小子
You mind your bottom, Paddy-boy.

68
00:07:32,787 --> 00:07:34,163
行动要快又准
Move sure and fast.

69
00:07:34,288 --> 00:07:35,832
你不是说过了吗？
You told me that, didn't you?

70
00:07:35,957 --> 00:07:37,667
我再叮咛一遍
So I'm telling you again.

71
00:07:38,709 --> 00:07:42,463
这次任务绝对非比寻常
This won't be like anything you've ever done before, little brother.

72
00:07:43,714 --> 00:07:45,800
目标现在离开王宫
Target leaving the palace now.

73
00:07:46,008 --> 00:07:47,009
好
Right.

74
00:07:47,218 --> 00:07:49,345
大伙打起精神，他们来了
Stay awake, lads. Here they come.

75
00:08:23,004 --> 00:08:24,088
这里行吗？
Okay right here?

76
00:08:24,172 --> 00:08:25,256
好看吗？
That good?

77
00:08:25,381 --> 00:08:27,216
再近点？
Any more? Little more?

78
00:08:27,341 --> 00:08:28,301
好
Okay.

79
00:08:28,384 --> 00:08:29,677
爸爸在那儿
There's Daddy.

80
00:08:41,022 --> 00:08:42,106
去！
Go!

81
00:08:46,861 --> 00:08:48,404
趴下！趴下
Down! Get down!

82
00:08:51,741 --> 00:08:52,867
准备好了
Ready!

83
00:08:53,951 --> 00:08:55,244
快卧倒！
Get down!

84
00:09:02,210 --> 00:09:03,419
快
Come on!

85
00:09:05,588 --> 00:09:07,548
快趴下
Get down. Keep her down!

86
00:09:17,099 --> 00:09:18,517
出来
Get out of the car!

87
00:09:18,601 --> 00:09:19,769
赶快
Come on!

88
00:09:19,894 --> 00:09:21,270
出来
Get out!

89
00:09:22,772 --> 00:09:24,315
把门打开
Open the fucking door!

90
00:09:25,441 --> 00:09:26,567
开门
Open it!

91
00:09:26,734 --> 00:09:27,777
杰克
Jack!

92
00:09:27,985 --> 00:09:30,238
开门，不然我就炸开
Open it, or I'll blow it off!

93
00:09:45,169 --> 00:09:46,629
我们走
Come on, let's go!

94
00:09:47,838 --> 00:09:49,257
快开
Go! Go! Go!

95
00:09:56,430 --> 00:09:57,598
帕迪？
Paddy?

96
00:10:07,108 --> 00:10:08,818
停下！放下武器
Stop! Army! Drop it!

97
00:10:32,717 --> 00:10:33,968
救救他
Help the boy.

98
00:10:38,848 --> 00:10:40,474
他已经死了
No, he's had it.

99
00:11:00,494 --> 00:11:02,455
没事的，宝贝，你待在这别动
It's all right, sweetie. I want you to stay here.

100
00:11:02,538 --> 00:11:04,832
马上就没事了
Everything's going to be okay.

101
00:11:08,711 --> 00:11:10,713
- 请往后站  - 退后，太太
- Stand back, please. - Stand back, ma'am.

102
00:11:10,838 --> 00:11:11,797
那是我丈夫
That's my husband.

103
00:11:11,881 --> 00:11:14,175
我是医生，我要去救治他
I'm a doctor. I'm going to treat him.

104
00:11:15,676 --> 00:11:17,386
天哪！杰克
Oh, Jesus, Jack!

105
00:11:17,511 --> 00:11:19,221
你当时怎么想的？
What were you thinking of?

106
00:11:21,557 --> 00:11:23,726
我要让你躺平，好吗？
I'm going to set you down, okay?

107
00:11:26,395 --> 00:11:28,022
保持清醒
Stay with me, Jack.

108
00:11:28,189 --> 00:11:29,899
听到吗？振作点
You hear me? Stay with me.

109
00:11:30,691 --> 00:11:31,692
杰克？
Jack?

110
00:11:32,026 --> 00:11:33,736
杰克，振作点
Jack, stay with me.

111
00:11:47,917 --> 00:11:50,127
人们对今天所发生的…
The feeling here today is one of outrage

112
00:11:50,211 --> 00:11:53,506
针对王室的恐怖攻击感到莫名的愤慨
over this unprecedented terrorist attack on the royal family.

113
00:11:53,589 --> 00:11:56,008
至今没有任何组织宣称对此事负责
And while no group has yet claimed credit,

114
00:11:56,092 --> 00:11:58,552
（警察局）根据目前种种猜测
there is, among many here, speculation already

115
00:11:58,636 --> 00:12:01,347
爱尔兰共和军涉有重嫌
of Irish Republican Army involvement.

116
00:12:01,430 --> 00:12:03,474
据目击者证实
According to eyewitness accounts,

117
00:12:03,557 --> 00:12:06,435
威廉・霍姆斯公爵，是皇后的表弟
Lord William Holmes, the Queen Mother's cousin

118
00:12:06,560 --> 00:12:08,604
和北爱尔兰国务大臣
and Minister of State for Northern Ireland,

119
00:12:08,729 --> 00:12:12,024
及其随行的妻儿得以幸免于难
along with his wife and son, would have most certainly been killed

120
00:12:12,100 --> 00:12:14,689
全因这位美国游客的仗义相助@
were it not for the heroic efforts of this man,

121
00:12:14,885 --> 00:12:16,400
约翰・帕特里克・雷恩
John Patrick Ryan,

122
00:12:16,612 --> 00:12:20,241
刺杀行动因他而告吹
the American tourist who broke up the assassination attempt.

123
00:12:20,328 --> 00:12:22,173
（中央情报局总部，维吉尼亚州兰利市）@

124
00:12:22,286 --> 00:12:23,910
他是一位作家
An author and professor

125
00:12:23,994 --> 00:12:27,206
（仅供阅读，不许复制）
也是美国海军官校的教授
at the United States Naval Academy in Annapolis, Maryland,

126
00:12:27,289 --> 00:12:29,667
雷恩是前海军中尉
Ryan is a former Marine lieutenant.

127
00:12:30,334 --> 00:12:32,837
他在枪战中受伤
Wounded in the exchange of gunfire,

128
00:12:33,003 --> 00:12:37,174
目前正在伦敦一家医院接受警方的监护@
he is listed in guarded condition at an undisclosed London hospital.

129
00:12:37,633 --> 00:12:40,344
我是黛博拉・韦斯顿，CNN新闻记者，伦敦报导
This is Deborah Weston, CNN news, London.

130
00:12:59,488 --> 00:13:00,823
对不起
I'm sorry.

131
00:13:01,323 --> 00:13:02,616
没关系
It's all right.

132
00:13:02,992 --> 00:13:04,827
你还活着，所以我原谅你
You're alive. I forgive you.

133
00:13:04,994 --> 00:13:06,370
不然…
Otherwise...

134
00:13:12,543 --> 00:13:13,961
小南瓜
Hey, pumpkin.

135
00:13:19,049 --> 00:13:20,301
我爱你
I love you.

136
00:13:23,846 --> 00:13:25,473
我也爱你
I love you, too.

137
00:13:28,976 --> 00:13:30,519
（英国皇家监狱，南华克）

138
00:13:33,481 --> 00:13:36,150
你的沉默也无法掩饰他们的怯懦
You dignify their cowardice with your silence.

139
00:13:36,734 --> 00:13:38,194
他们扔下你
They left you.

140
00:13:39,153 --> 00:13:40,988
舍下你扬长而去
They drove off without you.

141
00:13:43,324 --> 00:13:45,951
我不懂你干嘛还帮他们掩护
I'm curious as to what it is you think you owe them.

142
00:13:46,035 --> 00:13:49,747
如果我伙伴就这样把我丢下
If any of my mates ever drove off and left me in your hands,

143
00:13:50,331 --> 00:13:53,042
我不但不会跟他们讲义气
I'd not only feel no great sense of loyalty,

144
00:13:53,167 --> 00:13:55,669
还会亲手干掉他们
I'd make sure to remind meself to kill them.

145
00:13:58,005 --> 00:13:59,548
他们是谁，肖恩？
Who are they, Sean?

146
00:14:02,760 --> 00:14:04,345
他们在哪？
Where are they?

147
00:14:07,431 --> 00:14:08,557
行程是临时决定的的
The trip was unscheduled.

148
00:14:08,682 --> 00:14:11,519
你们怎么知道公爵会到那里？
How did you know Lord Holmes would be there?

149
00:14:22,738 --> 00:14:26,033
你不说话我就帮不了你
I can't help you if you don't talk to me, you know.

150
00:14:37,711 --> 00:14:40,839
我会把你的心挖出来喂你吃
I'd tear your heart out and serve it up to you with chips

151
00:14:40,920 --> 00:14:42,957
相信你一定会很享受的@
if I didn't know you'd enjoy it,

152
00:14:43,211 --> 00:14:44,920
你这个爱尔兰杂种
you Fenian bastard.

153
00:14:54,478 --> 00:14:56,564
绝对不会
No. Not in all eternity.

154
00:14:57,064 --> 00:14:59,775
他不会吐露半个字，肖恩・米勒不会的
He'll not chirp a word. Not Sean Miller.

155
00:15:00,234 --> 00:15:02,778
尤其是他们杀了他弟弟
And not while his brother is lying on a slab.

156
00:15:06,615 --> 00:15:09,285
怎么了，吉米？你不相信吗？
What's the matter, Jimmy? Don't you believe it?

157
00:15:09,785 --> 00:15:11,996
是整件事让人难以置信
It's the entire thing I don't believe.

158
00:15:12,079 --> 00:15:13,789
袭击王室，凯文？
The royal family, Kevin?

159
00:15:14,415 --> 00:15:17,251
这只让人们更加讨厌我们
You know that only turns people against us.

160
00:15:24,008 --> 00:15:26,594
而且这是擅自行动
Look, this was totally unauthorized,

161
00:15:27,428 --> 00:15:30,222
其他指挥官又知道行动是你策划
and the other brigade commanders, they know that you were behind it.

162
00:15:30,306 --> 00:15:31,849
去他的爱尔兰共和军
Fuck the bloody IRA.

163
00:15:32,182 --> 00:15:35,102
这么多年来一事无成
All these years of war, and they've got us nowhere.

164
00:15:36,186 --> 00:15:38,981
英格兰骨子里，仍是一个君主国
In its heart and soul, England is still a monarchy,

165
00:15:39,100 --> 00:15:40,758
为此我们必须打击
and that is where we must strike,

166
00:15:40,896 --> 00:15:43,724
皇室和统治阶层
at the royals and the ruling class.

167
00:15:47,364 --> 00:15:50,451
你如果不支持我们就是与我们为敌
You're either with us or you're against us, Jimmy-boy.

168
00:15:53,329 --> 00:15:54,705
自己决定吧
Make up your mind.

169
00:15:56,874 --> 00:15:58,334
我当然支持你们
Oh, I'm with you.

170
00:16:00,127 --> 00:16:02,671
好，我就是想听你这句话
Good. That's all I wanted to hear.

171
00:16:10,471 --> 00:16:12,014
我就不打扰你了
I'll leave you to it.

172
00:16:14,183 --> 00:16:15,476
凯文…
Kevin...

173
00:16:16,310 --> 00:16:18,212
查理今晚要过来@
Charlie's going to drop by tonight

174
00:16:18,297 --> 00:16:20,480
跟你把事情讲清楚
to try to straighten things out.

175
00:16:21,148 --> 00:16:23,317
聪明点，跟他谈谈
Be smart. Talk to him.

176
00:16:24,526 --> 00:16:26,487
控制一下脾气
And hold your temper.

177
00:16:28,656 --> 00:16:30,032
我答应你
I promise.

178
00:16:30,366 --> 00:16:31,867
多谢你，吉米
Thanks, Jimmy.

179
00:17:49,069 --> 00:17:50,279
凯文
Kevin.

180
00:18:01,915 --> 00:18:04,251
凯文，是我，查理
Kevin, lad, it's me, Charlie.

181
00:18:29,485 --> 00:18:32,154
这是我控制脾气的方式，吉米
That's me holding my temper, Jimmy-boy.

182
00:18:42,039 --> 00:18:43,832
上帝
Oh, God.

183
00:18:45,125 --> 00:18:46,460
哦
Oh, yeah.

184
00:18:46,668 --> 00:18:48,045
真好
All right.

185
00:18:52,966 --> 00:18:54,343
真好
All right.

186
00:18:56,845 --> 00:18:58,222
嗯
Oh, yeah.

187
00:19:04,686 --> 00:19:06,230
- 糟糕  - 怎么？
- Oh, damn! - What?

188
00:19:06,313 --> 00:19:07,815
- 我忘了  - 什么？
- I forgot. - What?

189
00:19:08,899 --> 00:19:10,484
我的皮包在哪？
Where's my bag?

190
00:19:11,860 --> 00:19:14,696
你不会是要我戴保险套吧？
You're not going to make me wear a rubber, are you?

191
00:19:15,197 --> 00:19:18,450
你没听教会说那是一种罪吗？
You know, the church says wearing one of them's a sin, darlin'.

192
00:19:18,534 --> 00:19:20,285
没错，亲爱的
So is this, darlin'.

193
00:19:41,681 --> 00:19:44,225
（欧代尔酒店）

194
00:19:56,864 --> 00:19:58,866
关于这个人…
So, what can you tell me about...

195
00:20:00,534 --> 00:20:01,702
你了解多少？
About this guy?

196
00:20:01,785 --> 00:20:05,038
肖恩？他是个好家伙
Sean? Oh, he's a nice boy, Sean Miller.

197
00:20:05,539 --> 00:20:07,457
在德里杀过一个神父
Shot a parish priest in Derry,

198
00:20:07,916 --> 00:20:09,626
而且是在告解的时候
during confession, if you can imagine.

199
00:20:09,710 --> 00:20:11,461
他以为神父是线人…
He thought the Father was informing for the British...

200
00:20:11,545 --> 00:20:12,504
抱歉，警官
Excuse me, Sergeant.

201
00:20:12,588 --> 00:20:16,341
我觉得对雷恩先生以及控方都没有任何好处
I don't think it's in Mr. Ryan's best interests or the prosecution's

202
00:20:16,425 --> 00:20:20,262
就是讨论和案情没有直接关联的事情
to discuss matters not directly related to the events at hand.

203
00:20:21,555 --> 00:20:25,100
你只要跟我确认照片中的人
If you can confirm for me that the man in that photograph

204
00:20:25,309 --> 00:20:27,895
就是广场上被你制服的人
is the same man you disarmed in the square,

205
00:20:27,978 --> 00:20:29,730
我们就问完了
I think we'll be through.

206
00:20:30,564 --> 00:20:31,732
就是他
I can.

207
00:20:33,400 --> 00:20:35,944
你还有什么要补充的吗？
Do you have anything to add, Mr. Ryan?

208
00:20:36,403 --> 00:20:37,446
有
Yes.

209
00:20:38,572 --> 00:20:41,325
- 我打死的是米勒的…  - 弟弟
- The man I killed was Miller's... - Brother.

210
00:20:41,408 --> 00:20:42,951
- 弟弟  - 帕特里克
- Brother. - Patrick.

211
00:20:43,452 --> 00:20:45,329
这小子还未满17岁
Not even 17, Paddy-boy.

212
00:20:47,122 --> 00:20:48,624
肖恩让他加入爱尔兰共和军…
Recruited by Sean into the IRA...

213
00:20:48,749 --> 00:20:50,334
你最后的证词…
Again, I think we'd all be better served

214
00:20:50,417 --> 00:20:52,878
要尽量清楚扼要
if we could preserve the clarity of your eventual testimony.

215
00:20:52,961 --> 00:20:54,546
我从报纸上得知…
I read it in the newspaper. I can hardly see...

216
00:20:54,630 --> 00:20:57,549
请不要看任何报纸
I'd appreciate you refraining from reading the newspapers.

217
00:20:57,633 --> 00:20:59,134
连环漫画都不能看？
Not even Doonesbury?

218
00:21:01,970 --> 00:21:04,097
还有要补充的吗？
Do you have anything to add?

219
00:21:05,974 --> 00:21:06,975
没有了
No.

220
00:21:07,767 --> 00:21:09,644
（恐怖分子审讯）

221
00:21:30,498 --> 00:21:31,708
在那边，先生

222
00:21:32,668 --> 00:21:33,752
- 雷恩先生？ - 是的
- Mr. Ryan? - Yes.

223
00:21:33,835 --> 00:21:34,920
我是杰弗里・沃特金斯
My name's Jeffrey Watkins,

224
00:21:35,003 --> 00:21:36,797
霍姆斯公爵的首席私人秘书
principal private secretary to Lord Holmes.

225
00:21:36,880 --> 00:21:38,382
很高兴见到您
It's a pleasure to meet you.

226
00:21:38,465 --> 00:21:39,675
- 这是我太太凯萨琳  - 您好
- This is my wife, Catherine. - How do you do?

227
00:21:39,800 --> 00:21:40,926
您好
Hello.

228
00:21:41,009 --> 00:21:43,303
雷恩医生，你的病人康复得怎么样了？
So, Dr. Ryan, how is your patient healing?

229
00:21:43,387 --> 00:21:44,596
还不错
Just fine.

230
00:21:44,680 --> 00:21:46,390
我们希望能尽快回家
We're looking forward to going home, though.

231
00:21:46,473 --> 00:21:47,599
我了解
I can imagine.

232
00:21:47,683 --> 00:21:49,643
这位是公爵阁下
May I introduce His Lordship?

233
00:21:49,726 --> 00:21:51,061
你好
Oh, hello.

234
00:21:51,645 --> 00:21:54,272
能与你见面我感到很荣幸，雷恩博士
It's my great honor to finally meet you, Dr. Ryan.

235
00:21:54,356 --> 00:21:55,482
谢谢
Thank you.

236
00:21:55,983 --> 00:21:59,528
您的救命之恩我无以为报
I owe you a debt of gratitude that I shall never be able to repay.

237
00:21:59,653 --> 00:22:01,488
谢谢，您太客气了
Not at all. Thank you for your kind note.

238
00:22:16,003 --> 00:22:19,673
真高兴你也能在此分享这个好消息，雷恩太太
I'm delighted that you're here to share in the good news, Mrs. Ryan.

239
00:22:20,048 --> 00:22:23,260
女王陛下决定为你的丈夫授予爵位
Her Majesty's decided to invest your husband KCVO,

240
00:22:23,719 --> 00:22:26,430
维多利亚爵士
Knight Commander of the Victorian Order.

241
00:22:28,432 --> 00:22:30,892
恭喜你，爵士
My congratulations, sir.

242
00:22:31,560 --> 00:22:33,520
- 谢谢  - 祝你今天好运
- Thank you. - Good luck today.

243
00:22:37,858 --> 00:22:39,109
杰克爵士？
Sir Jack?

244
00:22:41,570 --> 00:22:43,071
凯萨琳夫人
Lady Catherine.

245
00:22:51,747 --> 00:22:54,041
如果当时我有时间考虑
Perhaps if I'd had more time to think about it,

246
00:22:54,124 --> 00:22:56,585
我也许会选择采取别的方式
I would've preferred to do something else.

247
00:22:56,710 --> 00:22:59,004
你是说你没有时间，对不对？
So you're saying you didn't have time, is that it?

248
00:22:59,087 --> 00:23:00,172
对
That's correct.

249
00:23:00,255 --> 00:23:01,548
所以你没有？
So you didn't.

250
00:23:02,758 --> 00:23:03,842
没有什么？
Didn't what?

251
00:23:03,925 --> 00:23:05,302
考虑，先生
Think, sir.

252
00:23:05,427 --> 00:23:09,097
你想要表达的是你没有时间考虑
You didn't think is the point I believe you're trying to make.

253
00:23:09,720 --> 00:23:10,620
不对
No,

254
00:23:10,840 --> 00:23:14,217
而是你置身于一个情境之中
instead, you raced into a situation of which,

255
00:23:14,424 --> 00:23:17,100
正如你自己所言，是你自己不清楚的
by your own admission, you had no understanding,

256
00:23:17,731 --> 00:23:19,691
攻击我的当事人
attacked my client,

257
00:23:19,775 --> 00:23:22,778
实际上，他只是另一个匆忙上前帮忙的路人
who was, in fact, another pedestrian hurrying to help.

258
00:23:22,903 --> 00:23:24,196
戴着滑雪面罩？
Wearing a ski mask.

259
00:23:24,279 --> 00:23:28,116
你还击中另一个人的胸膛，这次…
Shot a second man in the chest, this one taking you, can it be...

260
00:23:28,241 --> 00:23:29,367
那是在他们朝我射击之后
After they shot me.

261
00:23:29,451 --> 00:23:32,537
你近距离开了三枪，打死了第二个人@@
three shots at point-blank range in order to fell the second victim.

262
00:23:32,621 --> 00:23:35,499
我是迫不得已才使用武力
I used that force I deemed necessary.

263
00:23:36,625 --> 00:23:38,251
我想是这样
I should say so,

264
00:23:39,628 --> 00:23:42,923
也相信法庭内所有人都会同意
and doubt very much whether anyone in this courtroom would disagree.

265
00:23:43,006 --> 00:23:44,216
对不起
Excuse me.

266
00:23:44,299 --> 00:23:45,717
此事非因我而起，先生
I didn't make this happen, sir.

267
00:23:45,801 --> 00:23:47,344
没有问题了
No further questions.

268
00:23:47,469 --> 00:23:48,637
是他引起的
He did.

269
00:23:49,096 --> 00:23:52,099
法官大人，还有一个问题
Oh, My Lord, there is one more question.

270
00:23:54,142 --> 00:23:56,103
雷恩博士，你是否仍然是…
Are you still, Dr. Ryan,

271
00:23:56,186 --> 00:23:59,272
中央情报局的雇员？
in the paid service of the Central Intelligence Agency?

272
00:23:59,981 --> 00:24:02,484
别忘记你宣过誓
I should remind you that you're under oath.

273
00:24:06,488 --> 00:24:08,156
- 不是  - 请再说清楚一点
- No. - I beg your pardon?

274
00:24:09,324 --> 00:24:10,450
不是
No.

275
00:24:12,160 --> 00:24:14,162
没有问题了，谢谢
That's all. Thank you.

276
00:24:15,455 --> 00:24:17,290
证人可以退席了
The witness may stand down.

277
00:24:17,457 --> 00:24:18,959
谢谢大家
Thank you very much.

278
00:24:20,836 --> 00:24:21,962
谢谢
Thank you.

279
00:24:22,879 --> 00:24:26,049
先生们，我想这是个适当的时机…
Gentlemen, I think this might be an appropriate moment...

280
00:24:26,508 --> 00:24:28,802
你很自豪，是吧？
Bloody proud of yourself, aren't you?

281
00:24:29,469 --> 00:24:32,347
你多管闲事
You stuck your nose in where it didn't belong.

282
00:24:32,639 --> 00:24:35,225
还杀了我弟弟
And now you've killed my baby brother.

283
00:25:23,899 --> 00:25:25,942
- 爸爸！  - 小南瓜
- Hey, Daddy! - Hey, pumpkin.

284
00:25:36,203 --> 00:25:39,080
你们真的长大了很多
Wow! You guys have really grown.

285
00:26:05,398 --> 00:26:06,900
感觉怎么样？
How are you feeling?

286
00:26:07,234 --> 00:26:08,610
不太好
Not so good.

287
00:26:08,944 --> 00:26:11,279
- 累了吗？ - 不是
- Tired? - No.

288
00:26:12,447 --> 00:26:15,992
完全不知道现在是几点，感觉像是早上
I have no idea what time it is. Feels like morning to me.

289
00:26:16,576 --> 00:26:17,953
那还用说
You're telling me.

290
00:26:21,081 --> 00:26:22,624
我错过什么了吗？
Did I miss something?

291
00:26:23,124 --> 00:26:24,167
没有
No.

292
00:26:25,252 --> 00:26:26,586
但我有
But I did.

293
00:26:30,632 --> 00:26:31,967
我怀孕了
I'm pregnant.

294
00:26:35,095 --> 00:26:36,137
亲爱的
Honey!

295
00:26:40,934 --> 00:26:43,436
我可以看会电视吗？我一点都不累
Can I watch some TV? I'm not at all tired.

296
00:26:47,649 --> 00:26:48,775
怎么了？
What?

297
00:26:51,111 --> 00:26:52,153
盘子
Plates.

298
00:26:53,822 --> 00:26:55,699
我有权利发表意见吗？
I don't have any say in this, do I?

299
00:26:55,782 --> 00:26:57,701
当然可以，宝贝，这是家庭
Sure, you do, honey. This is a family.

300
00:26:57,784 --> 00:26:58,952
人人都能发表意见
Everybody's got a say.

301
00:26:59,035 --> 00:27:00,996
但事情都已经发生了
But my say's after the fact.

302
00:27:01,830 --> 00:27:03,331
我说错了吗？
Or am I wrong?

303
00:27:03,498 --> 00:27:04,499
没有
No.

304
00:27:04,958 --> 00:27:06,167
你是对的
You're right.

305
00:27:07,168 --> 00:27:10,130
米凯拉真的很讨厌她妹妹
Michaela really despises her little sister.

306
00:27:10,505 --> 00:27:12,173
是吗？
Yeah?

307
00:27:12,507 --> 00:27:14,009
但事情可能会更糟
Are you ready for this? It could be even worse.

308
00:27:14,134 --> 00:27:16,344
也许是个小弟弟
It could be a baby brother.

309
00:27:16,469 --> 00:27:18,388
拜托，千万不要
Oh, no. Boys.

310
00:27:18,471 --> 00:27:20,932
你认为这些人恐怖分子吗？
I mean, do you refer to these fighting men as terrorists?

311
00:27:21,016 --> 00:27:22,475
不，他们是爱国者
No. We call them patriots.

312
00:27:22,559 --> 00:27:23,643
杰克
Jack.

313
00:27:23,727 --> 00:27:24,728
男孩子是…
Boys are...

314
00:27:24,811 --> 00:27:27,522
你是否否认这次行动…
Do you, in fact, deny that the Provisional Wing of the IRA

315
00:27:27,647 --> 00:27:29,441
是爱尔兰共和军所为？
was behind this assassination attempt?

316
00:27:29,520 --> 00:27:30,899
爱尔兰共和军会…
When the IRA...

317
00:27:31,255 --> 00:27:34,270
承认所策划的任何行动
carry out any form of campaign, they admit to it.

318
00:27:34,360 --> 00:27:35,075
谢谢你
Thank you.

319
00:27:35,194 --> 00:27:36,383
这是政策
That's the policy.

320
00:27:36,855 --> 00:27:38,570
他们会自豪地承认所作所为
They'll proudly say they did it.

321
00:27:38,992 --> 00:27:41,328
爱尔兰共和军出面承认了吗？
Have the IRA admitted to this?

322
00:27:41,870 --> 00:27:44,789
从常识、逻辑上或是种种其他原因…
I mean, common sense, logic, some form of reason...

323
00:27:44,873 --> 00:27:46,249
我能建议几个名字吗？
May I at least suggest some names?

324
00:27:46,333 --> 00:27:47,792
有人认为你在美国
Some think your efforts in America

325
00:27:47,876 --> 00:27:50,962
为爱尔兰的筹款事业会因此受影响…
raising money for the Irish cause will be affected...

326
00:27:51,046 --> 00:27:52,839
当然可以，宝贝
Sure you can, honey.

327
00:27:58,511 --> 00:28:01,514
（英雄勇救皇室成员）

328
00:28:32,212 --> 00:28:33,922
早上好，库利先生
Good morning, Mr. Cooley.

329
00:28:35,757 --> 00:28:37,133
夫人
And to you, madam.

330
00:28:37,258 --> 00:28:39,719
- 生意好吗？  - 很好，谢谢
- How is business? - Fine, thank you.

331
00:28:40,595 --> 00:28:43,807
我在一次遗产拍卖会上得到这本初版书
I came upon this first edition at an estate auction.

332
00:28:44,557 --> 00:28:46,226
你们师傅能修补吗？
Can your man restore it?

333
00:28:48,728 --> 00:28:50,188
你想何时要？
And when would you want this by, madam?

334
00:28:50,271 --> 00:28:51,272
尽快
Soon.

335
00:28:51,898 --> 00:28:53,166
（米勒的押解路线和车辆配备）

336
00:28:53,274 --> 00:28:55,443
这件事相当紧急
As you can see, it's very pressing.

337
00:28:56,444 --> 00:28:57,946
我不太清楚
I'm not sure.

338
00:28:58,238 --> 00:29:00,365
装订师傅未必做得来
The binder may have some trouble with this.

339
00:29:00,448 --> 00:29:01,616
是吗？
Is that so?

340
00:29:03,284 --> 00:29:04,619
我尽力而为吧
I'll see what I can do.

341
00:29:04,744 --> 00:29:06,538
你也知道他不是万能的
He's not a miracle worker, you know.

342
00:29:06,621 --> 00:29:09,457
当然，库利先生
No, obviously he's not, Mr. Cooley.

343
00:29:12,961 --> 00:29:14,963
就尽力而为吧
The best you can arrange, then.

344
00:29:17,465 --> 00:29:20,176
- 再见，库利先生  - 再见，夫人
- Good day, Mr. Cooley. - Good day, madam.

345
00:29:34,858 --> 00:29:35,900
喂，肖恩
Hello, Sean.

346
00:29:35,984 --> 00:29:38,486
你不介意我和你一起去吧？
Don't mind if I come along with you, do you?

347
00:30:26,659 --> 00:30:29,704
虽然我不同意你的所作所为
Although I disapprove of the things you've done, Sean,

348
00:30:31,206 --> 00:30:34,042
但我也不忍太过责怪你
I can't quite bring meself to condemn you.

349
00:30:39,672 --> 00:30:41,007
我不能
I can't,

350
00:30:42,592 --> 00:30:45,386
因为我明白仇恨的来源
because I understand where the hatred comes from.

351
00:30:47,847 --> 00:30:49,557
我非常明白
I more than understand it.

352
00:30:51,518 --> 00:30:53,978
但我们目前是处于
But the present fact is that we're very near now

353
00:30:54,062 --> 00:30:56,856
英国最黑暗的时期
the darkest hole in all of Great Britain,

354
00:30:57,899 --> 00:31:00,235
你却仍不肯开口
and you still won't speak to me.

355
00:31:28,721 --> 00:31:30,098
他们正在升桥
They're raising the bridge.

356
00:31:30,223 --> 00:31:32,225
我们五分钟后过去
We'll be here about five minutes.

357
00:31:32,392 --> 00:31:33,726
知道了
Understood.

358
00:31:54,122 --> 00:31:56,082
三号呼叫利明顿
Mobile Three, Lymington.

359
00:31:56,665 --> 00:31:57,792
利明顿

360
00:31:58,584 --> 00:32:00,753
他们干扰了无线电

361
00:32:10,847 --> 00:32:12,265
开门
Open the door!

362
00:32:13,141 --> 00:32:14,934
不然我就杀了他
Open it, or I'll kill him.

363
00:32:15,351 --> 00:32:17,478
- 他们抓了守桥人  - 我们怎么办？
- They've got the bridge keeper. - What do we do?

364
00:32:17,604 --> 00:32:19,355
- 开门  - 开门
- We open the door. - Open it!

365
00:32:19,522 --> 00:32:21,774
- 但是我的天啊！  - 但是什么？
- But for Christ's sake! - But what?

366
00:32:22,317 --> 00:32:25,278
等着他们杀了他再开门？
Wait until they kill him, then open the door?

367
00:32:33,453 --> 00:32:34,662
放下你们的武器！
Your guns!

368
00:32:34,787 --> 00:32:35,913
我们没有武器
We are unarmed.

369
00:32:35,997 --> 00:32:37,707
你们究竟是谁？
Just who the hell are you?

370
00:32:39,167 --> 00:32:40,627
带他们出来！
Get them out!

371
00:32:45,298 --> 00:32:46,799
低下头！
Get your heads down!

372
00:32:47,717 --> 00:32:49,677
全都趴在地上！
Lay down on the bloody ground!

373
00:32:49,886 --> 00:32:51,304
都不准动！
Don't you fucking move!

374
00:32:51,387 --> 00:32:54,182
你以为我们会忘了你吗？
Didn't think we'd forget about you, did you?

375
00:32:54,307 --> 00:32:55,808
感谢上帝
Honest to God.

376
00:33:00,180 --> 00:33:02,046
罗伯特・海兰警官@
Inspector Robert Highland,

377
00:33:02,548 --> 00:33:03,980
这是我的朋友
this is a friend of mine.

378
00:33:04,525 --> 00:33:06,486
我们终于见面了
We meet at last, Mr. Highland.

379
00:33:06,650 --> 00:33:10,262
他们给了你多少钱让你背叛自己的同胞？
Tell me, what did they pay you to turn against your own people?

